From 4e886acf7ab9fd0a517289481e253fd9883e7512 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ming Yen Hsieh <mingyen.hsieh@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 20 Dec 2023 17:21:36 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] wifi: mt76: mt7921: fix potential command timeout issues
 when suspend

An ongoing command may be interrupted if suspended, leading to a
command timeout. Add a lock to the suspend function in order to
protect the ongoing command from being interrupted.

Signed-off-by: Leon Yen <leon.yen@mediatek.com>
Signed-off-by: Ming Yen Hsieh <mingyen.hsieh@mediatek.com>
---
 mt7921/pci.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/mt7921/pci.c
+++ b/mt7921/pci.c
@@ -409,7 +409,9 @@ static int mt7921_pci_suspend(struct dev
 	if (err < 0)
 		goto restore_suspend;
 
+	mt792x_mutex_acquire(dev);
 	err = mt76_connac_mcu_set_hif_suspend(mdev, true);
+	mt792x_mutex_release(dev);
 	if (err)
 		goto restore_suspend;
 
